title: For Trade:  Vintage Bushnell and Hurricane both 4x32
postcontent: Bushnell Scopechief IV. Came off a rifle I traded for. I looked these up on the internet. Apparently from the early 70's and these were available in several magnifications and were their flagship models. It appears that Bushnell still honors their lifetime warranty on them as well. . Rings included, picatinny size. Internet forums give a value of $50-$60, I don't see it and would be happy with a 100 round box of high velocity 22, like Stingers, Mini-Mags, ect.Hurricane Optima found in grandpa's stash. Missing turret cap but functions. Has 1 original lense cap, lense cloth, and box. One end of the box has a piece of a Fred Meyer price tag. I do not know how old it is, guessing sometime in the 60's maybe 70's because that is when grandpa was last hunting. Rings (look cheap to me) included, looks like 3/8 Weaver. Further research tells that this is from the early 60's, possibly late 50's. Very well regarded Japan made. Believed to be made in the same factory as Bushnell and a few others, but I can not confirm that. Seeing as it is in such good shape, I had it on a 10/22 for one session but it is scratch and ding free, it seems like a natural to put on a similar vintage 22 for that sort of time period classic. Entertaining any reasonable trade offers.
